&lt;p&gt;Project Support Officer – Hywel Dda University Health Board&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fixed term post to 31st March 2022.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a Hywel Dda Health Board employee this post will only be offered on a secondment basis and you will need to have gained your line managers approval for the secondment prior to going to interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hywel Dda University Health Board is seeking to recruit an enthusiastic and motivated individual to support the Welsh Community Care Information System (WCCIS) Programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Project Support Officer will be responsible for supporting the WCCIS Project Managers in delivering the WCCIS programme working closely with the Programme and Project Managers to help deliver the programme to plan, monitor and report project progress.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WCCIS is the key digital enabler of fundamental transformation in health and social care and is a high profile programme within Hywel Dda supporting and enabling the transformation of Community based services across the region&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A proven track record of supporting IT related projects is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 24th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
